{{Quote|I've always thought that tie in novels were professionally produced fanfic&mdash;and if they're not, there's something wrong.|Karen Miller|<ref name="KMLJ">{{WebCite|url=http://karenmiller.livejournal.com/176639.html#t1511935|text=Thud!!!!|author=Karen Miller|work=[https://karenmiller.livejournal.com/ Karen Miller]|date=2009-05-27|archivedate=20160108074742}}</ref>}}
The term '''fanon''' refers to fan-made fiction. '''Fan fiction''' (also spelled '''fanfiction''' and often abbreviated '''fanfic''') is an unlicensed story written by a fan that takes place in an established fictional universe, such as ''[[Star Wars]]''.<ref name="Definition">{{WebCite|url=https://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=fanon|text=Fanon|work=[https://www.urbandictionary.com/ Urban Dictionary]|archivedate=20190506082127}}</ref> Such fiction is unrecognized by [[Lucasfilm]] and is therefore [[Canon|non-canon]].<ref name="wired">{{WebCite|title=Meet Leland Chee, the Star Wars Franchise Continuity Cop|url=https://www.wired.com/entertainment/hollywood/magazine/16-09/ff_starwarscanon?currentPage=all|work=[[Wikipedia:Wired (magazine)|''Wired'']]|date=2008-08-18|archivedate=20130616063450 }}</ref>

The term is a portmanteau of ''fan'' and ''canon''.

==Fanon made official==
{{Main|List of fanon elements in continuity}}
[[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]] authors occasionally adopted fanon. One instance of this was the [[501st Legion/Legends|501st Legion]], a [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone trooper]] [[unit]] that was named after a [[501st Legion (fan organization)|real charity organization]]. The fanon&mdash;or some elements of it, like the name in this case&mdash;thereby became part of Legends continuity.<ref name="Insider">{{InsiderCite|96|Inside the 501st}}</ref>

The ''[[What's The Story?]]'' competition invited members of the [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace fan club]] to submit fan-written backstories of selected characters, the best of which were accepted as their official backstories.<ref name="JCF">{{JCFCite|url=threads/20434695|board=Literature|thread=Official "What's the Story?" Hyperspace Databank Feature Discussion|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925162935/https://boards.theforce.net/threads/official-whats-the-story-hyperspace-databank-feature-discussion.20434695}}</ref>

On [[September 3]], [[2020]], user gomjabbar on the blog website [[:Wikipedia:Tumblr|Tumblr]] made a post that reads "every time a new Star War movie or show is announced all the fans are like 'OMG Glup Shitto is back 😭😭😭'."<ref name="GlupShitto">{{Tumblr|subdomain=gomjabbar|url=post/628276384757841920/every-time-a-new-star-war-movie-or-show-is|name=MOST THING GO OUT OF STYLE ‘CEPT ＦＲＩＥＮＤＳ|text=every time a new Star War movie or show is announced all the fans are like "OMG Glup Shitto is back 😭😭😭"|date=2020-09-03}}</ref><ref name="KYM">{{WebCite|url=https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/glup-shitto|text=Glup Shitto|work=Know Your Meme|archivedate=20250606042608}}</ref> After this post, the term "Glup Shitto" began to go viral, and became synonymous in circles of the ''Star Wars'' fandom with obscure characters that have names perceived by some as strange.<ref name="PolygonGlupShitto">{{WebCite|url=https://www.polygon.com/2020/12/18/22189448/who-is-glup-shitto-explained-star-wars-joke-meme|text=Star Wars fans’ favorite character, Glup Shitto, is back in the spotlight|author=Maddy Myers|date=2022-05-31|work=[[Wikipedia:Polygon (website)|Polygon]]|archivedate=20250127095625}}</ref> Some in the fandom have also taken to referring to some characters fitting this criteria as "their" Glup Shittos, placing an emphasis on their personal endearment or enjoyment of those characters.<ref name="GizmodoGlupShitto">{{WebCite|url=https://gizmodo.com/obi-wan-kenobi-episode-4-tera-sinube-glup-shitto-clone-1849042821|text=''Star Wars''' Glup Shitto Jig Is Up|author=James Whitbrook|date=2022-06-09|work=[[Wikipedia:Gizmodo|Gizmodo]]|archivedate=20250127095254}}</ref> On [[August 2]], [[2022]], [[Lucasfilm Story Group]] member [[Matt Martin]] acknowledged the Glup Shitto meme, stating that he had used the term in an official note.<ref name="MattMartinGlupShitto">{{Twitter|username=missingwords|url=status/1554614134330650625|name=Matt Martin - INACTIVE|date=2022-08-02|quote=Just used "Glup Shitto" in an official note|archivedate=20220802234449}}</ref>

